  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Business Development Manager (Diagnostics Services)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company’s Profile:</strong></p><p>Our client is a leading public healthcare institution that provides seamless, team-based care across all stages of a patient’s health journey. Serving a diverse community, they are committed to innovation, collaboration, and using technology to deliver person-centered, holistic care. Awarded as one of the Best Employers in 2025, they are looking for qualified individuals to join their dynamic environment dedicated to improving lives within the community.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Planning and executing initiatives and projects that support the strategic and operational goals of the Diagnostics Services team.</li><li>Partner with Diagnostics service leads to develop, implement, and maintain marketing and outreach efforts for the business unit.</li><li>Manage and respond to feedback from internal and external clients to support continuous service improvement.</li><li>Provide administrative, coordination, and professional support for business development activities and cross-functional projects.</li><li>Maintain and update the business unit’s internet and intranet pages, ensuring accurate content and timely enhancements based on user feedback.</li><li>Oversee and manage both new and existing contracts with internal and external stakeholders, including coordinating with the Legal team on any changes to terms and conditions.</li><li>Lead communication efforts and foster strong relationships with stakeholders by ensuring timely updates and clear dissemination of workflow-related changes.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>At least 2 – 3 years’ experience in business development, project coordination and stakeholder communication within the healthcare industry</li><li>Strong analytical skills and business acumen</li><li>Education qualification in any Business / Marketing field or equivalent</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Interested candidates may <strong>whatsapp your resume to 8977 7062</strong>. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.</p><p><br /></p><p>By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to the collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by company relating to this job application.</p><p><br /></p><p>Cassie Chan | R2197426</p><p>EnviroDynamics Solutions Pte Ltd | EA No: 12C6285</p>",
